  "title": "Project Manager (M&E / 5 Days)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Plan and oversee multiple engineering projects from concept to handover, ensuring they are delivered on time, within budget, with a strong focus on safety and quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Prioritize tasks and allocate manpower effectively to optimize resource utilization and meet project deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the preparation of tender bids for new projects while ensuring compliance with company policies and guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate and approve significant changes that affect project scope, budget, or schedule.</li>\n  <li>Lead complex or high-impact engineering projects, tracking progress and performance against the project plan.</li>\n  <li>Identify and address operational challenges promptly to reduce delays and maintain momentum.</li>\n  <li>Build, guide, and develop project teams with operational responsibilities to ensure alignment with business objectives and compliance with regulations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to both organizational and government safety standards, and maintain consistent delivery of customer safety and quality requirements.</li>\n  <li>Allocate capital and human resources strategically to enhance productivity and manage project expenditures and resources within budget.</li>\n  <li>Assess and authorize project investments that align with organizational needs and strategic goals.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
